<item>
            <title>[SOLR-6751] Analysis errors in DirectUpdateHandler2 throw ServerError exceptions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-6751</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you try and add a document with a docvalues field over 32k in length, lucene will throw an IllegalArgumentException.  DirectUpdateHandler2.addDoc() catches this, but then re-throws as a SolrException with a 500 error code, so any clients trying to distinguish between bad data errors and server status errors will do the wrong thing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
